  "text": "The LibreOffice core document model architecture is built on a foundation of five key C++ classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx, line 182): The base document shell class that serves as the foundation for all document types in LibreOffice. It inherits from SfxShell, SotObject, and IEmbeddedHelper, providing core functionality for document management, persistence, and integration.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx, line 196): The Writer (word processor) document class that represents the data model of a Writer document. This is the core document class for the Writer module, managing all document content and state.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class that encapsulates all spreadsheet data, formulas, and formatting. This is the central data structure for the Calc module.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338): The Impress/Draw document class that extends FmFormModel and manages presentation and drawing content, including slides, pages, and graphical elements.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103): The LibreOffice application framework entry point, implemented as a singleton that inherits from SfxShell. It manages global application state, window management, filters, and macro/scripting functionality.\n\nThese classes form the hierarchical architecture where SfxObjectShell is the common base, and each module (Writer, Calc, Impress/Draw) provides specialized implementations. SfxApplication provides the application-level framework that coordinates all these document instances."
}

